 For example, if we create a generic step to attach files the step definition
 may allow to define a text to show in the step like 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Add files for...
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 and the max number of files which can be added in the step.
 It should be a class inheriting from 
\family typewriter
StepDef
\family default
 class.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The 
\series bold
step instance
\series default
 regards all those options or actions that can be taken when the user access
 the step in the 
\family typewriter
tool-implementation
\family default
 portlet.
 For example in the previous case of a step to attach files, the step instance
 will manage the specific files added for a step in a particular tool instance.
 It should be a class inheriting from 
\family typewriter
Step
\family default
 class.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
These two classes should be packaged as 
\family typewriter
org.lrc.liferay.toolbuilder.steps.XXX
\family default
, where XXX is the name of the step, and should connect with the persistent
 layer, to be consistent with the rest of the portlet it is recommended
 to build the persistent layer with 
\emph on
Liferay Service Builder
\emph default

\begin_inset Foot
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
https://dev.liferay.com/develop/tutorials/-/knowledge_base/6-2/generating-a-persis
tence-framework-using-service-builder
\end_layout

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Besides the two core classes, some backing beans may be needed for the views.
 It is recommended to use 
\emph on
View Scoped
\emph default
 or 
\emph on
Request Scoped 
\emph default
beans and if some variable is needed to persist during the session save
 it in the 
\family typewriter
ToolSession
\family default
 bean, which is the 
\emph on
Session Scoped
\emph default
 bean and can be accessed from any other bean as a JSF 
\family typewriter
ManagedProperty
\family default
.
 It is important to note that all beans inherit from 
\family typewriter
AbstractBaseBean
\family default
.
 To maintain consistency with the rest of the portlet these beans should
 be packaged as org.lrc.liferay.toolbuilder.bean.steps.XXX, where XXX is the name
 of the step.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
On the other hand, and related to the views, at least two views should be
